Create KPI Columns, Measures and calendar Dimension 9

Create the following CONDITIONAL Columns IN YOUR QUERY EDITOR:

On your home page. click on Transform data. Then add column and conditional column.




1.

Race Name 

 if [race] = "B" then "Black" else

if [race] = "W" then "White" else

if [race] = "H" then "Hispanic" else

if [race] = "A" then "Asian" else

if [race] = "N" then "Native American" else

if [race] = "O" then "Other" else

if [race] = (blank) then "Other" 


NOTE: For the last race condition. do not type the (blank) rather leave it blank to represent when race is not indicated then other.

Also, the new column name for each of the three columns will be Race Name, KPI MENTALLY ILL AND AGE RANGE RESPECTIVELY. 


2.

KPI MENTALLY ILL 

if [signs_of_mental_illness] = true then 1 else

if [signs_of_mental_illness] <> true then 0


3

AGE RANGE  

if [age] <= 15 then 15 else

if [age] <= 20 then 20 else

if [age] <= 25 then 25 else

if [age] <= 30 then 30 else

if [age] <= 35 then 35 else

if [age] <= 40 then 40 else

if [age] <= 45 then 45 else

if [age] <= 50 then 50 else

if [age] <= 55 then 55 else

if [age] <= 60 then 60 else

if [age] <= 65 then 65 else

if [age] >= 66 then 70 


NEXT


Create the following Measures:

.ALL Killed = DISTINCTCOUNT('fatal-police-shootings-data'[id])

.SUM OF MENTAL KILLS = SUM('fatal-police-shootings-data'[KPI MENTALLY ILL])

.AVERAGE AGE = AVERAGE('fatal-police-shootings-data'[AGE RANGE])

.LY MIK = CALCULATE([.SUM OF MENTAL KILLS], SAMEPERIODLASTYEAR(CALENDER[Date].[Date]))

.VAR MIK = CALCULATE(([.SUM OF MENTAL KILLS] - [.LY MIK]))

MIK = DIVIDE([.SUM OF MENTAL KILLS], [.ALL Killed] ,0)

YOY = CALCULATE((DIVIDE([.VAR MIK],[.LY MIK],0)))


ADD A CALENDAR TABLE:

On your data page click add new table then use thus expression:


CALENDER = CALENDAR(DATE(2015,01,01),DATE(2020,12,31))

NEXT CLICK ADD COLUMN ON THE SAME CALENDAR TABLE AND ADD THESE COLUMNS ON THE CALENDAR TABLE

WEEKDAY NUM = WEEKDAY(CALENDER[Date].[Date],1)

Day of the week = FORMAT(CALENDER[Date].[Date], "dddd")

THEN SELECT THE Day of Week column and
click on the Sort-By-Column on the ribbon above and sort it by the weekday Num you just created
